            <title>[OAK-1334] TarFile initialized with wrong maxFileSize</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1334</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I think I found a bug in the way the FileStore initializes the TarFiles: the FileStore is initialized with a MB value (e.g. 256), and then calculates the actual byte size. However, it then still passes the MB value to the TarFile constructor, which doesn&apos;t convert MB to bytes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
